Assignment - 3 (Practice Question 3-6)

Suppose we have an online bookstore database and it has two tables: books and  warehouse.
 
The table books contain information such as BookId, Bookname, Warehouse_ID, Quantity
 
Similarly, the warehouse table contains Warehouse_ID, Address.
 
Using this information answer the following questions.
!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!






Question-27)Practice Question - 3
Send Feedback
What if we require the information of the books and where they are stored to get them ready for delivery. This would require the warehouse address, which is stored in a different table.How to get this data?

 

 Solution -:    We would require to join the two tables






Question-28)Practice Question - 4
Send Feedback
What if the books table has a huge amount of data, millions of entries. Will join still be an optimal solution?

 

 Solution -:    Solution Description
The performance of the system may decrease due to performing joins on large amounts of data.






Question-29)Practice Question - 5
Send Feedback
Can denormalisation be used in this scenario?

 

 Solution -:    Yes









Question-30)Practice Question - 6
Send Feedback
What should be done?

  

 Solution -:    Solution Description
If we add the address of the warehouse within the book table there would be no need to perform huge join operations.



  
